</i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usanthebmoonstare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santheb Moonstare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/20/02 3:05:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do Paladins Pull?</span><hr size=1> Archery sucks for a paladin.  Capped at 75.  Unless your doing a LONG distance pull its not worth it.<br><br>I pull with Cancel Magic =p <p>Santheb Moonstare--53rd level Cavalier of Rodcet Nife.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaallyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taallyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 266<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/20/02 3:23:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do Paladins Pull?</span><hr size=1> I never would have even used Archery if Cease had been available when I started my paladin.  Now, I always use Cease to pull. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69612">Baron Taallyn Nifesblade</a><BR>Seventh Cavalry<BR>Bristlebane</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaallyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taallyn</A> at: 7/20/02 3:24:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uriggorsmortus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RiggorsMortus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 546<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/20/02 4:49:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do Paladins Pull?</span><hr size=1> Cease because it has a relatively long range and costs very little mana - would use cancel magic when I have KEI possibly but I don't like spell slots (or even gear for that matter) for pulling.<br><br>I have a good bow but I haven't used it in many months because I got a nice range idol and bow and arrows are 2 slots I would rather have for lootz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wulfherehausakliufr>Wulfhere Hausakliufr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 983<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/21/02 2:28:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> pulling with a bow</span><hr size=1> Ifn yer using a Lull spell ter split a camp then pulling with a bow will be important. Tha time it takes ter recycle a Cease can take ter long. Fire a shot reet away for best chance o success on yer lull split.<br><br>Years ago ah did max ma archery ter 75 at level 16 by fear kiting skeletons in Butcherblock and Steamfront. Doing this was quite fun as ya learned how ter kite and how pathing works.<br><br>Yer skill ter hit yer target will fall ter nothing by level 30. No coincidence that it was also tha time we got oor first stun.<br> <p>Wulfhere Hausakliufr<BR>Hammer o Brell, Rallos Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 521<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/22/02 11:36:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pulling with a bow</span><hr size=1> Paladins *can* pull with a bow, but whether they prefer to or not I would say is level dependent.  Generally I agree that pulling with cease (or cancel magic) is the preferred method, at least at high levels.<br><br>What I don't know for sure is how that balances out at low levels.  With your lower mana pool and meditation skill, the cease spell might take a bigger chunk out of your mana and take longer to regain.  Since bows don't use mana it might be more efficient to use those, although to be fair you have to figure in any lost fighting time to replace arrows.<br><br>Bows are also longer range (at least with long range arrows) than a cease would give you, although you could argue that cease has enough range for most situations.<br><br>Bow skill doesn't really come into play for pulling, it really doesn't matter if you miss or do very little damage, your goal is just to aggro the mob.<br><br>I don't carry my bow with me anymore, I almost never have a situation where I would use it, but I did use it when I was at lower levels.  Admittedly this was before cease/desist were added, maybe I would have chosen differently if I had those.<br><br>If you want to pull from really long range, or very quickly, bows will do better than spells.  With my long range bow (darkwood) and long range arrows (range 150 dmg 1), I was able to hit mountain giants in Frontier Mountains from so far away that they actually wouldn't come after me until I got closer to them--I could see the animation of the arrows hitting them, but they would just stand there until I moved up.  With the even longer range Luclin bows (I haven't made one yet), you could go even further than that.  <br><br>Situational, to be sure, but I'm sure that sort of thing has its place.  One example might be pulling hill giants in RM when it's overcamped and you're fighting for pulls with other groups. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Duke Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umileron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mileron</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/22/02 2:06:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Pulling...</span><hr size=1> I pull (have pulled) a variety of ways as my paladin.<br>Recently, in EW doing ulthorks, etc, I use my pet rangeress.  Rather, I run out, if I see two together, I wait for them to split, hit one with Lull, and shoot the other.  If there's only one, I'll cease it, and shoot it as I run back to camp.<br>In CC, I was lull-pulling all the time, even stuff I wanted to pull.  (Those terrors have some wacked pathing if you're standing one foot to the right or the left.)<br>At times, such as the giant fort in Warsliks or Frontier, I was using strictly proximity aggro - getting close enough for it to aggro me and stun/root them on the way back.  Was nice having mobs all lined up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><table border="1" width=87% bordercolor="0000FF"><tr><td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95465">Mileron</a></td><td>Minstrel</td><td><a href="http://www.kenned.com/chp">Crusaders of the High Plains</a></td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=116169">Immarrana</td><td>Knight of Prexus</td><td>Xegony</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=172913">Bramilnar</a></td><td>Wardermaster of Marr</td><td> (Click names for Magelo)</td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=blackwaite>Blackwaite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/24/02 7:43:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling...</span><hr size=1> I usually Lull if needed, pull with a long range arrow, and root any unwanted mobs.  That usually give the party time to take care of the first mob before the second arrives..<br><br>Blackwaite Chapelheart <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/roguehill/Blackwaite3.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaladril1961.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galadril1961</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 409<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/24/02 8:06:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling...</span><hr size=1> I am always a proponent of maxing all your combat skills and archery is no exception. <br><br>There are alot of different uses for a bow that don't require you to have a high skill, but you should be able to get your skill to 75 with just normal use through the lower levels. <p><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=278009>Galadril Adamante</a><BR>Officer, Order of the White Dragon<BR>Knight of Tunare<BR>Bristlebane Server<BR><a href=mailto:sblue@bright.net>sblue@bright.net</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaladmera1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daladmera1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/24/02 10:07:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How NOT to Pull</span><hr size=1> DO NOT TRY TO PULL WITH FLASH OF LIGHT!<br><br>I tried this at 18 in Unrest on yard trash.  The death beatle ran, then went around the front of the house.  Soon, after discussing his fear of me with every mob in the yard, he came back.  Closely followed by everything in the yard. <p><c>-== Brothers on Tholuxe Paells ==-<br>Daladmera Fleshreaver lvl 53 Paladin <br>Daladmera Buhtaysmakaa lvl 48 Cleric <br></c></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueumerin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eumerin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 227<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/24/02 2:32:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How NOT to Pull</span><hr size=1> To reiterate the above, there is only one use for FoL as a pulling device that I can think of, and it works like this.<br>In OOT, I was with a couple of others killing aviaks, and I used FoL to split the spawn.  The blinded one would run away (same direction EVERY time - this is important, because it meant the aviak would never wander into other mobs that might agro), while the other would agro.  By the time FoL wore off, and the missing aviak came back, the one we were fighting would be dead.<br>Other than a highly situational circumstance like that, don't use FoL to pull.<br> <p><table width="350" border="0"><tr><td width="144"><div align="center"><img src="http://www.geraldfield.com/nadinesplace/calvinquiz/spiff.gif" width="142" height="125" align="absmiddle"></div></td><td><div align="center"><b><font size="3">You are Spaceman Spiff!</font></b><br><font size="2">Zounds! You are the intrepid Spaceman Spiff, the engaging explorer ensconsed in an unending universe of exotic and evil extraterrestrials! You're brave, but you should give that dictionary a rest.<br><font size="1">Take the <a href="http://www.geraldfield.com/cgi-bin/unofficial/quizzes/sfesurvey.cgi?whatcalvinareyou" target="_blank">What Calvin are You? Quiz</a> by <a href="mailto:contessina_2000@yahoo.com">contessina_2000@yahoo.com</a>!</font></font></div></td></tr></table><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96807 target="web">Eumerin Paxodus</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaeronvalorne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeron Valorne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/25/02 4:12:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling</span><hr size=1> Hi guys.  There's another way to pull.  If you're just a touch inside max range that you can land lull and you cast it and it fails, it sometimes single pulls the target.  Lull is designed to be low aggro when it lands.  If it fails, it remains low aggro but can single pull the one mob it lands on.  Remember lull is designed to not aggro the mobs around the target.  <br><br>Mobs aggroing and passing aggro is a function of lvl difference between the target and you, distance between you and the target (with no action), aggro radius of the action on the target, and distance between the target and adjacent mobs.  Mess around with those aspects (and I would suspect others I'm not thinking of right now) and you'll learn a lot. <p><b><font color="#000080" size="4">Daeron Valorne</font><br><font size="2">Paladin of the <font color="#FF0000" size="3">59</font><font size="2">th Trial</font></b> <br>Rodcet Nife<br><i>"To protect the sanctity of life and hold truth, honor and courage above all else."</i><br><br>Aewyn - Druid of 44 seasons<br>Draekos - Iksar Monk of the 47th rung<br>Vexz - Iksar Shaman of the 47th order</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 542<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/26/02 5:49:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>DO NOT TRY TO PULL WITH FLASH OF LIGHT!<br><br>I tried this at 18 in Unrest on yard trash. The death beatle ran, then went around the front of the house. Soon, after discussing his fear of me with every mob in the yard, he came back. Closely followed by everything in the yard. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Sounds like a wonderful way to AE (Area of Effect) pull Unrest.  Sound crazy?  AE groups aren't just for 60s.  With the help of my druid and enchanter I leveled up a cleric alt to about 35, mostly doing AE in Unrest and Sol A in off hours.  It is the fastest way to powerlevel I have seen to date.  <br><br>In Unrest I was just using my Cleric's AE direct damage spells, using the druid to buff/heal and the enchanter to buff/stun--I think a full AE group in Unrest would be a blast. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Duke Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhaldurincalkhldir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haldurin Calkhldir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/26/02 7:26:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2vw5m/sigport.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling</span><hr size=1> Hmm, I use my bow to pull all the time.<br><br>I have the  low end new Tunare only bows, 20dam/40dly range 200 5 str 5 wis.<br><br>Coupled with a simple range 150 arrow, i can pull from further away than any spell could try.<br><br>Last nite I was grouped with a cpl friends, one is a lvl 48SK (Only grouped cuz he is a good RL friend, otherwise, I stay away from evils, or at least try to).<br><br>He was pulling with whatever spell they have, lifetap/draw whatever.<br><br>He saw a wurm (we were in BW) he wanted to pull, but there were junk mobs between us.<br><br>I trotted up, aimed and fired.  Pulled the wurm over the other (non allied) mobs and got 4 shots off by the time we got back to the pull slot.<br><br>Scored ~60pts on the wurm before he got close enough to hit us.<br><br>If you have a good bow, bows are worth it.  Without this fancy bow, maybe I would cease pull.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucardiacarrest100.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cardiacarrest100</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/26/02 9:45:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling</span><hr size=1> bow pull if mob is farther than 200ft, also lower agro. cancel magic if its self buffed, flame of light to do initial damage to stop it from attacking another group's puller.  usually bow pull because you can shoot while running and it doesn't use mana.<br>failed pacify pull works sometimes in dungeons, but its risky when there is no enchanter around.<br><br>Baron <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=233648">Zeal</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> &lt;Sanctus Lumen&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uasegai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Asegai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/27/02 6:58:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm